# Licensing

Gravital-Steward is dual-licensed by component. Each crate declares its license
in its `Cargo.toml` `license` field; this file summarizes the split.

| Component | License | File |
|---|---|---|
| Core runtime crates (`steward-core` and the execution crates) | AGPL-3.0-or-later | [LICENSE-AGPL](LICENSE-AGPL) |
| Protocol and client SDK crates (`steward-proto`, `steward-sdk`) | Apache-2.0 | [LICENSE-APACHE](LICENSE-APACHE) |
| Documentation and examples | Apache-2.0 | [LICENSE-APACHE](LICENSE-APACHE) |

## Why this split

- **AGPL-3.0-or-later for the core** protects the runtime against being offered
  as a closed-source hosted service without contributing changes back.
- **Apache-2.0 for the protocol and SDK** maximizes integrability: anyone can
  build clients, agents and tooling against the wire protocol without copyleft
  obligations.

See [docs/adr/ADR-0002-licensing.md](docs/adr/ADR-0002-licensing.md) for the
full rationale.

